    <h3>2. Hero Section</h3>
    <h1>The Promised Truth Has Arrived</h1>
    <p>Discover the divine message and the fulfillment of ancient prophecies through the prophesied successor.</p>
    <button>Learn More</button>

    <h3>3. About Us</h3>
    <p>The religion of peace and light, Ahmadism, is founded by the Qa'im of the household of Muhammad and Abdullah Hashem Abas al-Sadiq (as) and Imam Mahdi (a.f.s.) to fulfill prophecies foretold in the scriptures of the Abrahamic faiths. It was prophesied by the Prophet Muhammad's holy family that this faith would rise in the End Times.</p>

    <p>Ahmadi faith is referred to in the traditions of Muhammad and his family as the “new religion” which is brought forth by Imam Mahdi (a.f.s.) and the Qa'im from his lineage, to fill the world with justice as it had been filled with injustice.</p>

    <p>23 years ago, the signs of these prophecies became clear when Imam Ahmad al-Hassan (a.s.) emerged in 1999 in Basra, Iraq, calling all people as a messenger from Imam Mahdi, and the prophesied Yamani of the Prophet’s family.</p>

    <h3>4. Divine Message & Law of Successorship</h3>
    <h4>Card 1: Establishing the Foundations</h4>
    <p>Imam Ahmad al-Hassan (a.s.) established this faith by reviving people's connection with their Creator. He came with truth, revealing a divine plan that mankind may return to God: the Law of Successorship.</p>

    <h4>Card 2: Law of Successorship</h4>
    <p>The Law of Successorship, mentioned in the Qur'an and the story of creation, teaches that every divine messenger must:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Be appointed by God and referenced by prior prophets.</li>
      <li>Possess divine knowledge of all things.</li>
      <li>Call towards God and His governance – for only God appoints successors.</li>
    </ol>

    <h4>Card 3: Fulfilling the Criteria</h4>
    <p>Only Imam Ahmad al-Hassan (a.s.) fulfilled all three criteria, backed by the Prophet Muhammad's will which names him – Ahmad son of Abdullah (the spiritual son and rightful successor).</p>

    <h3>5. Fulfillment of Prophecies</h3>
    <h4>Section 1: Emergence of the Yamani</h4>
    <p>23 years ago, signs of the prophecy’s fulfillment appeared when Imam Ahmad al-Hassan (a.s.) emerged in Basra in 1999, claiming to be a messenger of Imam Mahdi and the prophesied Yamani.</p>

    <h4>Section 2: The Will of the Prophet</h4>
    <blockquote>
      "Then there shall be twelve Mahdis after him. When death approaches him, let him hand over to his son, the first of the Mahdis – he has three names: like mine, my father's, and he is Abdullah (servant of God), Ahmad (praised), and the Mahdi (the guided)." – Ghayba al-Tusi
    </blockquote>
    <p>This sacred will was the foundation of this divine call, led by Abdullah Hashem Abas al-Sadiq (a.s.) as the historical establisher of this faith. The call rejected worldly authority, calling to divine sovereignty and became a unique theological source never seen before.</p>
